#Text=Japan beats Aussie Spirit in first two games of series
#Text=Saturday , March 24 , 2012
#Text=Jodie Stevenson of the Aussie Spirit during game one .
#Text=Image : LauraHale .

#Text=Hawker , Canberra — Wednesday night , the Japan women 's national softball team picked up victories in the first two games of their international test series against Australia by scores of 3-2 and 5-3 .
#Text=Aussie Spirit player during game one .
#Text=Also pictured number 11 Rie Nishiyama of Japan .
#Text=Image : LauraHale .
#Text=The first game , at 17:30 AEST ( 6:30 UTC ) , began with Vanessa Stokes pitching for Australia .
#Text=Japan 's third batter in the first inning , Rie Nishiyama , was walked .
#Text=Yuikiyo
#Text=Mine was next to bat , and a wild pitch allowed Nishiyama second base .
#Text=Mine went on to hit a double on a long hit to the outfield , which enabled Nishiyama to score the only point of the first , as Japan went in 1-0 up .
#Text=In Australia 's half of the first , batters faced Yamato Fujita .
#Text=Stacey Porter led off with a hit .
#Text=Verity Long-Droppert bunted out but advanced Porter to second .
#Text=Brenda De Blaes came up to bat and Porter stole third base .
#Text=De Blaes was then walked .
#Text=Chelsea Forkin made a base hit , scoring Porter .
#Text=Stevenson got a hit to load the bases .
#Text=The first ended when Jodie Bowering hit a pop out that was converted into a double play .
#Text=Japan went scoreless in the top of the second .
#Text=In Australia 's half , Clare Warwick led off , hit the ball into her own leg and worked off the pain .
#Text=The Japanese pitcher subsequently walked her .
#Text=Stacey McManus flied out .
#Text=Bowering bunted out but advanced Warwick .
#Text=Porter was walked .
#Text=Long-Droppert came to bat with runners on first and second , got hit by ball and took her base .
#Text=During De Blaes 's at bat , there was a wild pitch that allowed a run to score .
#Text=De Blaes hit a bouncer to the outfield , and was thrown out on a fielder 's choice to end the inning 2-1 for Australia .
#Text=Leigh Godfrey of the Aussie Spirit during game one .
#Text=Image : LauraHale .
#Text=The Japanese answered back during the top of the third .
#Text=Stokes was still pitching for Australia when a run scored .
#Text=The game remained scoreless until the top of the seventh .
#Text=Designated player Yukina Seki led off the inning by being struck out .
#Text=Yamada hit a triple .
#Text=Right fielder Kawano was thrown out at first but scored Yamada to bring the game to 3-2 .
#Text=Mani Souma made a base hit to get second .
#Text=The inning ended when Kazuki Watanabe struck out .
#Text=Australia was not able to answer back in the bottom half of the seventh and lost the game .
#Text=The second game originally had a scheduled start time of 19:30 AEST ( 8:30 UTC ) but did not get underway until 20:05 AEST ( 9:05 UTC ) .
#Text=The game was scoreless going into the top of the fourth , with two outs , when Shizuyo Hamamoto hit a home run for Japan .
#Text=Haruka Fujino then was out to end the inning .
#Text=The Japanese would score again in the top of the fifth .
#Text=Australia answered back in their half of the inning .
#Text=Melinda Weaver led off with a double .
#Text=Warwick made a hit , advanced the runner to third but was ultimately out in a run out .
#Text=Stacey Porter was walked .
#Text=Michelle Cox hit out but not before advancing the runner to second .
#Text=De Blaes hit a double to score two runs and tie the game up .
#Text=Leigh Godfrey went out and the inning ended .
#Text=The game remained tied at the end of regulation play .
#Text=International rules for ties were used .
#Text=These involved a runner starting on second .
#Text=Each side would score in their half of the inning , to bring the game to 3-3 after eight .
#Text=At the top of the ninth , Japanese player Hamamoto started on second .
#Text=Nishiyama grounded out but advanced Hamamoto to third .
#Text=Haruna Sakamoto was walked .
#Text=Hamamoto went home on a wild pitch during Misa Okubo 's at bat that also saw Nishiyama advance to third .
#Text=This brought the game to 4-3 .
#Text=Okubo singled to score Nishiyama bringing the score to 5-3 .
#Text=The next two batters went out to end the inning .
#Text=Australia was unable to answer back in the bottom of the ninth .
